/// Real references data.

/// Real references type.
(rRefs) [. [f]if];

/// Constructor.
///
/// A start point is the index in closes of the date when a change of position
/// sold-bougth happens.
///
/// The first change of postion registered must be, at maximun,
/// 'cts.realReferenceDateIx' days before the last closes date.
///
/// The first calculus of a rRefs start with 'index = -1' and 'reference = -1.0'.
///
/// After calculating new real references from an array of closes, a start point
/// and its reference value, if a new start point of calculus is found, it is
/// retuned in 'dateIx' and its reference value in 'rref'.
///
/// In case of not finding a new start point, values of index and reference do not
/// change, but they are '-1' and '-1.0'. In such case both values are set to
/// valid values.
///
///   Refs   : Real references.
///   dateIx : Index of closes corresponding to the 'rref' date.
///   rref: Real reference value corresponding to the close.
//: [. [f]if]
new : Refs, dateIx, rref;
